# Terrible Gerald's — project rules

## Stack
- Client: Vite, React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind (admin only), Auth0
- Server: Express, Mongoose, MongoDB Atlas
- Legacy reference: `legacy/astro-dist/` (Astro v4 static export)

## Layout
- Public marketing UI → `client/src/pages/public/`, `client/src/components/public/`
- Admin CMS → `client/src/pages/admin/`, `client/src/components/admin/`
- API models → `server/src/models/`
- Public API → `server/src/routes/`
- Admin API → `server/src/routes/admin/` (always `checkJwt` + `requireAdmin`)

## Content types
Event, MenuItem, Faq, SiteContent, ContactSubmission — see `docs/architecture/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## When editing public pages
- Fetch dynamic data from API (`contentApi.ts`), not hard-coded copy
- Reuse existing legacy CSS variables (`--tg-red`, `--font-headline`)
- Images live in `client/public/images/`

## When editing admin
- Use Tailwind utility classes consistent with existing admin pages
- Wire CRUD through `adminApi.ts`
- Protect routes via `ProtectedRoute` in `App.tsx`

## Env
Never commit secrets. Templates: `.env.example`, `client/.env.example`, `server/.env.example`
